@VicenteSegundo In this case, please contact our customer service on messenger, live chat or phone so that we can assist you further with this. Our contact information can be found here: https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Warm regards,
Jenny

@DeeTravels2022 If the number is unreachable for you, please contact the airport's general number and there ask to be transferred to the baggage staff onsite. You can also visit our bag service at the airport for faster handling.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@Blozzer1892 Hello! We are very sorry for the inconvenience! Unfortunatly the security control at the airport is experiencing high pressure at the moment. If you miss your flight due to the queues, please visit one of our ticket desks onsite for assist.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@KristinaNyber19 Hello! We are very sorry for the long handling time from our customer care at the moment. I have sent a reminder to them regarding your case, and they will reply to you by email as soon as possible.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@DeeTravels2022 Hello! We are very sorry for the inconvenience! For assist with the delayed baggage, please contact our baggage staff in London on number +44 344 3754250. 

Warm regards,
Jenny

@blackapinay Hello! We publish flights ca 300-330 days before departure.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@mia_se Hello! Check in and bag drop must be done the same day as departure and earliest at 4 am when check in/bag drop open for the day.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@Mohabdilah Hello! For assist, please contact our live chat or phone. Our contact information can be found here: https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Warm regards,
Jenny

@piniacolada22 Hello! We are very sorry for the long waiting time on our phones at the moment! For assist with name change you can also contact our live chat. It can be found here: https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj

Warm regards,
Jenny

@susiel51 Hello! We are truly sorry about this! If the bag is delayed/missing, please contact our bag handling staff in Tromsö on number +47 772 80 400 or +47 900 60 664 so that they can help you to track your bag.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@VicenteSegundo Hello! If you have a refundable voucher, and it has been 12 months since it was issued, you can ask for a refund of the remaining amount here: https://t.co/ui2Ls6yWKm Open the voucher and there should be an "apply for refund" link.

Warm regards,
Jenny

@YasminBauer2 Hello! Unfortunatly, we do not handle lost or delayed baggage through the customer service. For assist with the baggage, please contact any of the numbers in the link. You can also file a missing bag report here: https://t.co/7iWu2adlLd

Warm regards,
Jenny

@PaulChoquette8 Hi, what web browser are you using on your iPhone and Macbook? We recommend using Google Chrome and also please make sure no VPN or proxy network is activated on your devices.

Best regards,
Anton.

@JeremyGeorgeJG If you have already tried this and still experience the same issue I would recommend you to contact Amex to see why the payment is not finalized when you tried to book.

Best regards,
Anton.

@gemlouisetaylor Hi, in this case the options are to either wait for more information to appear in Worldtracer, when delivery is possible you will also be informed directly on email/sms. Or try calling baggage service again later.

Best regards,
Anton.

@gemlouisetaylor Hi, baggage service has access to the systems used to localize baggage, but I don't know if they will have more information than Worldtracer for your individual case.

Best regards,
Anton.

@Franklioni Hi, I am not sure why you are getting this error message. I recommend that you try to clear cache/cookies in your web browser, using Google Chrome is recommended. After clearing cache/cookies you can try to book again.

Best regards,
Anton.

@JeremyGeorgeJG Hi, I am not aware of any payment errors in our SAS app currently. I recommend that you try clearing cache in the app and try again. If the problem persists, try booking on our website instead to see if that helps.

Best regards,
Anton.

@kuhnmo Hello, sometimes online check-in is not possible for certain flights, in these cases you need to check-in at the airport instead.

Best regards,
Anton.

@ZivatheAussie Hi, unfortunately we are unable to look into individual cases over Twitter. I recommend that you try contacting Baggage service support for assistance https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2

Best regards,
Anton.

@YasminBauer2 Hello, we are sadly not able to assist with delayed baggage cases through Twitter. I recommend that you contact Baggage service on the phone for assistance https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2

Best regards,
Anton.

@loulockwood Hi, we are unfortunately no able to assist with individual cases through Twitter. Please contact us on Livechat https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj or FB Messenger with your case ID and we can help you take a look at this.

Best regards,
Anton.

@jorgenborg Hello, the airport check-in and bagdrop at Arlanda opens at 04:00.

Best regards,
Anton.

@goodhill685 Hello, we are not able to assist with delayed baggage errands through Social media, I recommend you to call Baggage service support for assistance, phone numbers available at https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2

Best regards,
Anton.

@astoks Hi, I am sorry to hear that your baggage is delayed. If you have received a file reference please use Worldtracer https://t.co/2zwsPbhQFU to trace your bag. For assistance you can contact Baggage service, phone numbers are listed at https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2

Best regards,
Anton.

@johanhaglund You can find our live-chat and phone number here: https://t.co/b3QIqPk7bj If you contact us there we can help you rebook the flight. 
I recommend you delete your tweet since it has your personal booking reference, so it doesn't end up in the wrong hands. 
Kind Regards, Natasha

@ueliason Om du har svårt att nå fram på telefon har vi även en live chatt som du kan hitta här: https://t.co/z4gOZAAJQJ 
Jag rekommenderar att du tar bort din tweet då du har med din personliga bokningsreferens i den, så att den inte hamnar i fel händer.
Vänliga hälsningar, Natasha

@ChristianLenz If you have reported the delayed baggage here: https://t.co/ojhL9dIf2x you can track it here: https://t.co/2zwsPbhQFU 
For further information, I recommend contacting Baggage Service, you can find their phone number via this link: https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2 
Kind Regards, Natasha

@samanthahardim8 If you follow this link: https://t.co/ZV9bTO3uo2 you can find the phone numbers available for Baggage Service at different airports. You call the phone number for the airport you landed at, and they should be able to help you report the delayed baggage. 
Kind Regards, 
Natasha
